<!-- MAIN -->
<main class="main">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="hero" id="overview">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">DEVELOPER DOCUMENTATION</div>
    <div class="hero-title">NEXUS</div>
    <div class="hero-sub">UNIFIED FINANCIAL TERMINAL — v5.0</div>
    <p class="hero-desc">
      Nexus is a self-contained, single-file Bloomberg-style financial terminal built in vanilla JavaScript.
      No build step, no framework, no backend required — open the HTML file in any browser and it runs.
      This document covers every module, the API integration layer, the design system, and how to extend the terminal with new panels.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-badges">
      <span class="badge badge-green">SINGLE FILE</span>
      <span class="badge badge-amber">10 MODULES</span>
      <span class="badge badge-blue">6 API SOURCES</span>
      <span class="badge badge-red">DEMO MODE — NO KEY REQUIRED</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- QUICK START -->
  <section id="quickstart">
    <div class="section-label">GETTING STARTED</div>
    <h2>QUICK START</h2>
    <p>
      Nexus ships as a single <code>Nexus_v5.html</code> file. There is no install process.
      In demo mode (default) all data is procedurally generated — no API keys are needed.
    </p>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="step-title">OPEN THE FILE</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Double-click <code>Nexus_v5.html</code> or drag it into Chrome, Firefox, or Safari. The terminal boots immediately — no server needed.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="step-title">EXPLORE DEMO MODE</div>
          <div class="step-desc">All 10 modules work out of the box with simulated data. The status bar shows <code>DEMO — MOCK DATA</code>. Prices refresh every 2.5 seconds, maps animate, the dark pool tape streams live.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="step-title">ADD API KEYS (OPTIONAL)</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Open the file in a text editor. Find the <code>NEXUS_API</code> object near the bottom of the <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag. Replace <code>'DEMO'</code> with real keys to activate live data. See the API Setup section for each provider.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <div class="step-title">UNCOMMENT REAL API CALLS</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Each module that supports live data has a commented-out real API call sitting directly above the demo data fallback. Uncomment it and delete the mock generator call below it.</div>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <div class="callout callout-info">
      <div class="callout-title">NOTE — LOCAL FILE CORS</div>
      <p>When opened as a local file (<code>file:///</code>), browsers block cross-origin fetch requests. To use real API calls, either host the file on any HTTP server (<code>python3 -m http.server 8080</code>) or use a browser extension that disables CORS for local development.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DEPENDENCIES -->
  <section id="dependencies">
    <div class="section-label">GETTING STARTED</div>
    <h2>DEPENDENCIES</h2>
    <p>Nexus loads three external libraries from CDN. All are loaded in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>. No npm, no bundler.</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>LIBRARY</th><th>VERSION</th><th>PURPOSE</th><th>CDN</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Chart.js</td><td>4.4.0</td><td>All line, bar, doughnut, radar, and scatter charts across every module</td><td>cdnjs.cloudflare.com</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Leaflet.js</td><td>1.9.4</td><td>Interactive maps in the Aircraft, Vessel, and Traffic tracking modules</td><td>cdnjs.cloudflare.com</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Google Fonts</td><td>—</td><td>Orbitron (display/logo) and Share Tech Mono (monospace UI)</td><td>fonts.googleapis.com</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="callout callout-warn">
      <div class="callout-title">OFFLINE USE</div>
      <p>If you need the terminal to work offline, download Chart.js and Leaflet locally and update the <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> tags to point to the local files. The Google Fonts can be replaced with system monospace fonts by editing <code>--mono</code> and <code>--display</code> in the CSS variables.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider"/>

  <!-- STRUCTURE -->
  <section id="structure">
    <div class="section-label">ARCHITECTURE</div>
    <h2>FILE STRUCTURE</h2>
    <p>The entire terminal lives in one HTML file. The internal structure is divided into four logical blocks:</p>
    <pre><code><span class="c-com">Nexus_v5.html</span>
<span class="c-com">|</span>
<span class="c-com">+-- &lt;head&gt;</span>
<span class="c-com">|   +-- CSS Variables (design tokens)</span>
<span class="c-com">|   +-- Component styles (topbar, nav, modules, overlays)</span>
<span class="c-com">|   +-- Module-specific styles (one block per module)</span>
<span class="c-com">|</span>
<span class="c-com">+-- &lt;body&gt;</span>
<span class="c-com">|   +-- .topbar       (logo, ticker tape, AI button, alerts)</span>
<span class="c-com">|   +-- .master-nav   (all tab buttons, clock, LIVE indicator)</span>
<span class="c-com">|   +-- .app          (container for all module panels)</span>
<span class="c-com">|       +-- #home, #dashboard, #orderbook, #news</span>
<span class="c-com">|       +-- #tracking, #aircraft, #vessels</span>
<span class="c-com">|       +-- #risk</span>
<span class="c-com">|       +-- #options, #darkpool, #macroheat, #correlation</span>
<span class="c-com">|   +-- Overlay panels (AI modal, alerts panel, portfolio editor)</span>
<span class="c-com">|</span>
<span class="c-com">+-- &lt;script&gt;</span>
<span class="c-com">    +-- NEXUS_API config object</span>
<span class="c-com">    +-- Utility functions (rnd, rndInt, pick, mkChart, nexusFetch)</span>
<span class="c-com">    +-- Shared data (DASH_ASSETS, PORTFOLIO_D)</span>
<span class="c-com">    +-- Module init functions (one per module)</span>
<span class="c-com">    +-- switchModule() — central router</span>
<span class="c-com">    +-- DOMContentLoaded boot block</span></code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- MODULE SYSTEM -->
  <section id="modules">
    <div class="section-label">ARCHITECTURE</div>
    <h2>MODULE SYSTEM</h2>
    <p>
      Modules are <code>div.module</code> elements. Only one is visible at a time — controlled by the <code>active</code> class.
      All modules use <strong>lazy initialization</strong>: they only boot when first clicked, not on page load. This keeps startup time fast regardless of how many modules exist.
    </p>

    <h3>HOW SWITCHING WORKS</h3>
    <pre><code><span class="c-fn">switchModule</span>(<span class="c-str">'dashboard'</span>, btn)
<span class="c-com">// 1. Removes .active from all .module divs</span>
<span class="c-com">// 2. Adds .active to #dashboard</span>
<span class="c-com">// 3. Sets currentModule = 'dashboard'</span>
<span class="c-com">// 4. If not yet initialized, calls initDashboard()</span></code></pre>

    <h3>INITIALIZATION FLAGS</h3>
    <p>Each module has a boolean flag that prevents double-initialization:</p>
    <pre><code><span class="c-kw">let</span> dashInitialized = <span class="c-kw">false</span>;
