  <!-- API CONFIG -->
  <section id="api-config">
    <div class="section-label">API SETUP</div>
    <h2>API CONFIGURATION</h2>
    <p>
      All API keys live in one object at the top of the <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> block.
      Find it by searching the file for <code>NEXUS_API</code>.
    </p>
    <pre><code><span class="c-com">// ---- LOCATE THIS BLOCK IN Nexus_v5.html ----</span>
<span class="c-kw">const</span> <span class="c-key">NEXUS_API</span> = {
  <span class="c-key">polygon</span>:      <span class="c-str">'YOUR_POLYGON_KEY'</span>,      <span class="c-com">// stocks, options, forex</span>
  <span class="c-key">alphavantage</span>: <span class="c-str">'YOUR_ALPHAVANTAGE_KEY'</span>, <span class="c-com">// macro indicators, FX</span>
  <span class="c-key">coingecko</span>:    <span class="c-str">''</span>,                      <span class="c-com">// crypto (no key needed)</span>
  <span class="c-key">fred</span>:         <span class="c-str">'YOUR_FRED_KEY'</span>,         <span class="c-com">// economic data</span>
};</code></pre>

    <h3>NEXUSFETCH — THE API HELPER</h3>
    <p>Every real API call goes through <code>nexusFetch()</code>. It adds a 5-second timeout and automatically falls back to mock data if the request fails, so the terminal never breaks even with an invalid key.</p>
    <pre><code><span class="c-kw">async function</span> <span class="c-fn">nexusFetch</span>(url, fallbackData) {
  <span class="c-kw">try</span> {
    <span class="c-kw">const</span> ctrl = <span class="c-kw">new</span> <span class="c-fn">AbortController</span>();
    <span class="c-kw">const</span> tid  = <span class="c-fn">setTimeout</span>(() => ctrl.<span class="c-fn">abort</span>(), <span class="c-num">5000</span>);
    <span class="c-kw">const</span> r    = <span class="c-kw">await</span> <span class="c-fn">fetch</span>(url, { signal: ctrl.signal });
    <span class="c-fn">clearTimeout</span>(tid);
    <span class="c-kw">if</span> (!r.ok) <span class="c-kw">throw new</span> <span class="c-fn">Error</span>(<span class="c-str">'HTTP '</span> + r.status);
    <span class="c-kw">return await</span> r.<span class="c-fn">json</span>();
  } <span class="c-kw">catch</span> (e) {
    console.<span class="c-fn">warn</span>(<span class="c-str">'[NEXUS] falling back to demo data:'</span>, e.message);
    <span class="c-kw">return</span> fallbackData; <span class="c-com">// terminal keeps working</span>
  }
}</code></pre>

    <h3>HOW TO ACTIVATE A REAL API CALL</h3>
    <p>Each module has a commented-out real call sitting above its mock generator. The pattern is always the same:</p>
    <pre><code><span class="c-com">// --- BEFORE (demo mode) ---</span>
<span class="c-com">// const url = `https://api.polygon.io/v2/aggs/ticker/${sym}/...`;</span>
<span class="c-com">// const data = await nexusFetch(url, null);</span>
<span class="c-com">// if (data && data.results) { /* parse */ }</span>

<span class="c-key">optionsData</span> = <span class="c-fn">genOptionsChain</span>(sym, price); <span class="c-com">// &lt;-- DELETE THIS LINE</span>

<span class="c-com">// --- AFTER (live mode) ---</span>
<span class="c-kw">const</span> url  = `https://api.polygon.io/v2/aggs/ticker/${sym}/...`;
<span class="c-kw">const</span> data = <span class="c-kw">await</span> <span class="c-fn">nexusFetch</span>(url, <span class="c-kw">null</span>);
<span class="c-kw">if</span> (data && data.results) {
  optionsData = <span class="c-fn">parsePolygonOptions</span>(data.results);
}</code></pre>
  </section>

