  <!-- EXTENDING -->
  <section id="extending">
    <div class="section-label">REFERENCE</div>
    <h2>ADDING A NEW MODULE</h2>
    <p>Follow this exact pattern to add a new module without breaking any existing functionality.</p>

    <h3>STEP 1 — ADD THE NAV BUTTON</h3>
    <pre><code><span class="c-com">&lt;!-- Inside the relevant .nav-group in .master-nav --&gt;</span>
&lt;button class="mtab" onclick="<span class="c-fn">switchModule</span>(<span class="c-str">'mymodule'</span>, this)"&gt;MY MODULE&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>STEP 2 — ADD THE HTML PANEL</h3>
    <pre><code><span class="c-com">&lt;!-- Inside .app, after the last existing module --&gt;</span>
&lt;div class="module" id="mymodule"&gt;
  <span class="c-com">&lt;!-- your module content --&gt;</span>
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>STEP 3 — ADD THE INIT FLAG AND FUNCTION</h3>
    <pre><code><span class="c-kw">let</span> mymoduleInitialized = <span class="c-kw">false</span>;

<span class="c-kw">function</span> <span class="c-fn">initMyModule</span>() {
  <span class="c-com">// build your module's content here</span>
  <span class="c-com">// set up any intervals, charts, or event listeners</span>
}</code></pre>

    <h3>STEP 4 — REGISTER IN SWITCHMODULE</h3>
    <pre><code><span class="c-com">// Inside the switchModule() function, add one line:</span>
<span class="c-kw">if</span> (id === <span class="c-str">'mymodule'</span> && !mymoduleInitialized) {
  <span class="c-fn">setTimeout</span>(() => { <span class="c-fn">initMyModule</span>(); mymoduleInitialized = <span class="c-kw">true</span>; }, <span class="c-num">80</span>);
}</code></pre>

    <div class="callout callout-info">
      <div class="callout-title">CHARTS IN NEW MODULES</div>
      <p>Always use <code>mkChart(canvasId, config)</code> rather than <code>new Chart()</code> directly. The helper tracks and destroys previous instances, preventing the "canvas already in use" error that occurs when a user navigates away and back to a module.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TROUBLESHOOTING -->
  <section id="troubleshooting">
    <div class="section-label">REFERENCE</div>
    <h2>TROUBLESHOOTING</h2>

    <h3>TABS / BUTTONS NOT WORKING</h3>
    <p>This is almost always a JavaScript error that silently halts execution. Open the browser console (F12 > Console) and look for red errors. Common causes: a syntax error in an added code block, or a missing DOM element that a function tries to manipulate on boot.</p>

    <h3>MAPS NOT RENDERING</h3>
    <p>The Leaflet map modules use <code>requestAnimationFrame</code> to defer initialization. If the map appears blank, call <code>trackMap.invalidateSize()</code> after the container becomes visible. This is already handled in <code>switchModule</code> for the built-in map modules.</p>

    <h3>CHARTS NOT UPDATING</h3>
    <p>If a chart stops refreshing, check that <code>currentModule</code> matches the module's ID string exactly. A typo in the module ID string will cause all <code>setInterval</code> guards for that module to silently skip.</p>

    <h3>API CALLS FAILING SILENTLY</h3>
    <p>All API failures fall back to demo data via <code>nexusFetch</code> — the terminal won't show an error. Add a <code>console.log</code> in the catch block of <code>nexusFetch</code> or open the Network tab in DevTools to see the actual HTTP response and status code.</p>

    <h3>CORS ERRORS ON LOCAL FILE</h3>
    <p>Browsers block cross-origin requests from <code>file:///</code>. Run a local server:</p>
    <pre><code><span class="c-com"># Python 3</span>
python3 -m http.server 8080

<span class="c-com"># Node (npx)</span>
npx serve .

<span class="c-com"># Then open:</span>
http://localhost:8080/Nexus_v5.html</code></pre>

    <h3>OPTIONS CHAIN SHOWS NO DATA</h3>
    <p>Enter a ticker that exists in <code>DASH_ASSETS</code> (AAPL, MSFT, NVDA, TSLA, etc.). The options chain generator uses the asset's price from that array. An unknown ticker will still work but will generate a chain around a randomly chosen price.</p>

    <div class="callout callout-ok">
      <div class="callout-title">DEVTOOLS WORKFLOW</div>
      <p>The most useful DevTools panel for debugging Nexus is the Console (for JS errors) combined with the Network tab (for API calls). Filter the Network tab by <code>Fetch/XHR</code> to see only the API requests and their response status codes.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

<script>
// Sidebar active link highlight on scroll
const sections = document.querySelectorAll('[id]');
const links = document.querySelectorAll('.sb-link');

const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
  entries.forEach(entry => {
    if (entry.isIntersecting) {
      links.forEach(l => l.classList.remove('active'));
      const active = document.querySelector(`.sb-link[href="#${entry.target.id}"]`);
      if (active) active.classList.add('active');
    }
  });
}, { rootMargin: '-20% 0px -70% 0px' });

sections.forEach(s => observer.observe(s));
</script>
